            <p class="head-headlineSmall"><b>CURRENT</b></p>
            <p><b><a href="centennial/1915/index.html">A Centennial Celebration of <i>The Birth of a Nation</i></a></b><br>
            An overview of the most-important film of 1915 — perhaps, of the entire silent era.</p>
            <p><a href="newZealandRepatriation.html"><b>75 American Films to Be Repatriated for Preservation</b></a><br>
            The New Zealand Film Archive and the National Film Preservation Foundation announce major silent film recoveries.</p>
            <p><b><a href="hayakawaFilms.html">Eye Film Instituut Nederland Discovers Unique Films Starring the Silent Hollywood Star Sessue Hayakawa</a></b><br>
            The surviving footage of three Hayakawa features have been preserved by the film archive.</p>
            <p><a href="geh-frick.html"><b>George Eastman Museum Appoints Dr. Caroline Frick</b></a><br>
            Loughney becomes new curator of motion pictures at the respected film archive.</p>
            <p><a href="unknownFilm1.html"><b>Help Identify These Unknown Films 1</b></a><br>
            Take a look at some frame enlargements. You may recognize an unidentified film or its cast.</p>
            <p><b><a href="unknownFilm2.html">Help Identify These Unknown Films 2</a></b><br>
            You might recognize unidentified films from these descriptions.</p>
            <p><b><a href="unknownFilm3.html">Help Identify These Unknown Films 3</a></b><br>
            Take a look at frame enlargements on a Hungarian site to possibly identify American and European films.</p>
            <p><b><a href="unknownFilm4.html">Help Identify These Unknown Films 4</a></b><br>
            View an excerpt from an unidentified film produced by Carl Ledermann & Co.</p>
            <p><b><a href="publish.html">Silent Era : Publish</a></b><br>
            An extensive publishing project from Silent Era.</p>
            <p><b><a href="tenthAnniversary.html">The 10th Anniversary of the Silent Era Website</a></b><br>
            Editor and publisher Carl Bennett shares a few thoughts about the website’s history and future goals.</p><!-- #BeginLibraryItem "/Library/Table-HorizontalLine.lbi" --><table background="../img/horizontalLine.gif" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" height="13" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></table><!-- #EndLibraryItem --><p class="head-headlineSmall"><b>RESOURCES</b></p>
